Tahini Cupcakes with Chocolate Tahini Frosting
  --Molly Yeh
  
Cupcakes:
2 c sugar
2 1/4 c flour
1 1/2 tsp baking powder
1 1/2 tsp baking soda
1 1/2 tsp kosher salt
1/4 tsp cinnamon
2 large eggs
1 c buttermilk
1 tbsp vanilla
2 tbsp flavorless oil, like canola
6 tbsp tahini
3/4 c water

Preheat oven to 350F. Line and grease two cupcake pans and set them aside. In a large bowl, combine all dry ingredients. In a medium bowl, combine eggs, buttermilk, vanilla, oil, and tahini. Add the wet ingredients to the dry ingredients and mix to combine. stir in the water. Pour into cupcake pans and bake until a toothpick inserted into the center of one comes out clean. Begin checking for doneness at 18 min. Let cool for a few minutes in the pans and then transfer to a wire rack to cool fully.

Frosting:
1 c unsalted butter, softened
3/4 c tahini
3/4 c unsweetened cocoa powder
2 c powdered sugar
1/2 tsp vanilla extract
a pinch of kosher salt
a pinch of cinnamon

Beat together the butter and tahini. Beat in the cocoa powder, and then the powdered sugar. Add vanilla, salt, and cinnamon. Taste and make adjustments as desired. Frost cooled cupcakes.
